description:
lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/slip_transport.c:671

k_thread_create(&s_rx_thread, ...) is called without capturing or checking its return value. Per Zephyr docs, it returns thread ID or negative errno on failure (e.g. -ENOMEM for stack). This can lead to silent failure of RX thread, causing is_ready true but no RX processing. Should be:

int ret = k_thread_create(...);
if (ret < 0) {
    LOG_ERR("Failed to create SLIP RX thread: %d", ret);
    return ret;
}

Fix as real work per task. Discovered in codereview pass 1.
